Recipe

-Coco powder: 4 tbsp
-Baking soda: 1/2 tsp

latestPosts.caption:
So basically this chocolate cake is gluten and vegan free and can be consumed by everyone ❤️ 

✨Comment down below which recipe you guys want me to bake next✨

*Ingredients*

*For dry ingredients*
-Gluten free Oats: 1.5 cup
-Cocoa powder: 1/4 cup
-Baking powder: 1 tsp
-Baking soda: 1/2 tsp 
-Salt a pinch 
-Jaggery powder: 3/4 cup 

*For wet ingredients*
-Ripe Banana: 2pcs
-Lemon juice: 1 tsp
-Oil: 1/2 cup
-Soy milk: 1/2 cup
-Vanilla essence: 1 tsp
-Dried fruits/Seeds

👇 TIPS & TRICKS 👇

-Substitute jaggery powder with regular jaggery / coconut sugar of same proportion

-Can increase or reduce the amount of Jaggery as per taste buds or as per you banana's sweetness

-Roast the oats before using it

-Before buying oats do check whether it's gluten free or not

-Substitute lemon juice with vinegar of same proportion

-Substitute soy milk with water / regular milk / any plant bases milk

-Substitute vegetable oil with coconut oil (if that's okay for you)

-Substitute 2 bananas with 1 egg (but not sure as I'm vegetarian) or by vegan or regular curd of 1/4 cup 

-Vanilla essence is optional

-Don't cut cake when it's warm. Leave it for 30mins atleast before slicing otherwise it will crumble

-If you're okay using xantham gum to your gluten-free cake just to give texture or structure to the cake then DM me

-Can bake this cake in cooker or kadhai without put sand or salt below cake tin, just put a small plate or katori upside and place the cake tin over it and bake it how you usually bake cakes. And if you're baking cake in kadhai or any vessel then keep small gap while covering it with plate just to pass the warm air and to avoid sticky cake surface 

-Never overmix batter after adding dry ingredients, mix until it combines

-Bake in kadhai or cooker for 30-35mins in low flame

-Bake in oven/otg at 170°C for 30-35mins 

-Every oven works different so it might bake fast or slow..so keep an eye after 30mins 🙃

Rainy days call for crispy cravings 🌧️✨
Nothing beats the cozy comfort of hot, crunchy Lonavala-style Corn Bhaji while the rain pours outside ☕🌽
Perfectly spiced, super crunchy, and made for chai-time indulgence, this one's a monsoon must-try

☘️ Ingredients ☘️
-Bhutta/Corn: 1pc (1 cup)
-Green chilli: 2 nos
-Garlic: 1/2 inch
-Salt per taste 
-Kashmiri chilli powder: 1/4 tsp
-Corn flour: 1 tbsp 
-Besan: 3 tbsp
-Coriander leaves: 2 tbsp 
-Water as per need
-Ajwain(optional)
-Onion+Capsicum (optional)

🌧️ Baarish Ke Zaayke, EPISODE: 1 💫
Guilt-Free Instant Tikki Chaat. A quick, healthy & full of flavor 😋

Monsoon cravings hit hard, right? But this time, no aloo, no deep-fry,  just a delicious, light chaat that comes together in minutes and makes your rainy day even better. ☔✨

Perfect for chai-time, cozy balcony vibes, or just when you want something chatpata but healthy too 🫶

I usually crave aloo tikki in the rain, but I wanted to try something different, and trust me, yeh wali chaat dil jeet legi ❤️

✨ INGREDIENTS ✨ 
-Roasted Oats: 1/2 cup 
-Soaked Poha: 1/2 cup
-Carrot: 1/2 cup (can more/any veggies of choice)
-Paneer: 1/4 cup
-Onion: 1 big 
-Ginger: 1 inch
-Green Chilli: 1 nos
-Cumin Seeds: 1/4 tsp
-Salt per taste 
-Ghee as per need
-Sweetened Dahi
-Green Chutney
-Dates Chutney
-Sev
-Pomegranate 

✨Process ✨
-Add all the ingredients and blend it until combines, now shape into tikkis and shallow fry or air fry by brushing some ghee on top and bake at 170°C for 5mins

-Assemble everything in a leaf bowl with some curd, chutney and your toppings, and enjoy ✨

Try it out, tag someone you’d love to share this with, and tell me.. baarish mein aapka comfort food kya hai? 🌽🍵🍛

Stop buying store bought almond flakes and them at home instead😍
 

☘️ Slicer comes with a gripper, so it's safe to use but I personally like slicing directly without gripper. 

☘️Soak the almonds for 5-6hrs before shredding 

☘️For skinless almond flakes remove the skin and dry it for 5-10mins before shredding 

☘️For skinned almond flakes dry the soaked almonds for 10-15 mins so that the almond skin gets firmed and doesn't peel off while slicing 

☘️ Comment "link" for slicing machine link

☘️The slicer comes with adjustable slicing thickness, so you can adjust the thickness of the blade as per your need

☘️After slicing dry the almond flakes before storing (dry it in oven or airfryer)

☘️Use the flakes in cornflakes or as a cake sprinkle or mithai sprinkle

☘️For pistachio flakes follow the same process
